00:00:00.700 --> 00:00:03.790
Of course, we came across transparency when we talked about middleware and

00:00:03.790 --> 00:00:07.840
we listed various kinds of transparency that was appropriate to middleware

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:12.930
situations. In general, transparency suggests providing interfaces that enable

00:00:12.930 --> 00:00:17.740
client code to be written without having to be concerned with specific details.

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:21.130
Of course, this generality comes with a cost of extra design and testing work.

